translated: Dahr, Elisabeth, principal, Jönköping, b. 27/10/95 in Jönköp, daughter of elementary school inspector Robert J and Jenny Wigh. — Completed secondary school in Stockholm in 1914, received a Bachelor's degree in Lund in 1915, a Master's degree in 1917, completed teaching degree for elementary school in Stockholm in 1918, Licentiate degree in 1925, qualified for service as a regular teacher in secondary schools and teacher-training colleges in 1928. Worked as a substitute and subject teacher at Jönköp. elementary school from 1918-1919, became a regular teacher in 1919, became head of girls' high school in Jönköp. for several schools from 1925, became subject teacher and principal of Jönköp. municipal girls' school in 1935. Member of the city council (Free People's Party) from 1935 and its preparation committee from 1935-1943, member of the girls' school committee since 1938 and the school investigation committee since 1940, member of the board of Fil:- and psykohlär. fören., chairman of the Girls' and Co-ed Teachers' National Association in 1947.
